			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Anyone tested out giving their pets a high damage weapon to see if they can increase their max dmg they can do?  I tried this out with giving my pet a defenders lightblade, which is 22dmg 34dly.  I also gave him another weapon that was 20dmg but I can't remember the name of it.  Anyways, not only did it not increase his max dmg per hit, it also seemed to not effect his overall dps.  He was still missing the same amount and hitting for what seemed like a normal amount of damage.  Has anyone tested it out with higher dmg weapons?
<br />

<br />
I remember giving my pets high damage weapons from lvl 1 to 60 and ti effecting them greatly. Even giving a pet a 12dmg weapon at lvl 60 increased their max dmg. Why would they change it on the higher end pets?  If they did change it so that atk doesn't help the pet anymore, why then are they giving us a GoD AA that increases atk.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
