				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Nilaman wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">As far as I remember, the ONLY weapons that effected a pets hits (aside from old skool necro pets) were high damage 2h weapons before the pets could dual wield.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
Correct.  Unless they've drastically changed things and I didn't hear about it, pets have two choices for damage.  They will <span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="text-decoration: underline">ALWAYS</span></span> use the greater of these two values to determine their maximum hit:<ol type="1"><li> Natural/focused maximum hit
<br />
<li> Weapon damage * 2</ol>For example, pet that hits for 40 should not see any damage increase from being given a 12 damage weapon (12*2&lt;40), but a pet that hits for 16 should(16&lt;12*2).  That's why giving a summoned staff of tracing to a level 8 pet was such a good idea... it increased max hit from 12(natural) to 14(weapon_dmg*2).
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>MarloonCyphres wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Nah, I remember giving my lvl 51 earth pet two 12dmg piecers from grimlings in TM. the dmg increase was a lot</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
Unless your 51 earth pet hit for less than 24 max damage, that should not be true.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>MarloonCyphres wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">If they did change it so that atk doesn't help the pet anymore, why then are they giving us a GoD AA that increases atk."</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
Not sure where that came from, but atk helps <span style="font-style: italic">all</span> melee, including pets.  And what GoD AA are you looking at that increases a pet's atk?  I've heard flurries, crits, and defensive stuff... a raw atk-increase would be strange.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
